    <body>
        <p>Click in any of the individual fields (<span class="Emphasis">Left</span>, <span class="Emphasis">Right</span>, <span class="Emphasis">Top</span>, <span class="Emphasis">Bottom</span>) to specify the settings for the padding. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet5">This adds extra space between an image's border and the image itself. </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet8">This adds extra space between a text box's border and the text within it. </MadCap:conditionalText>In the left side of the field, enter a number for the amount of padding. In the right side of the field, select a unit of measurement (e.g., point, pixel, centimeter) for the number you entered. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Styles/More_About_Styles_and_Style_Sheets/About_Units_of_Measurement.htm">About Units of Measurement</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
